{"questionId":"22710190","questionHtml":"<p>Show that it is not possible for the spectator to ever get a T-shirt.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>use of their arithmetic sequence from (a)(ii) with <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>40</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong><em>(M1)</em></strong></p>\n<p>coordinates of seat <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mn>40</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>69</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>21</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>6</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>EITHER</strong></p>\n<p>substitution of their <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>69</mn></math> into their <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>5</mn><mn>882</mn></mfrac><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>44</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn></math> from part (e)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(M1) </strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>5</mn><mn>882</mn></mfrac><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>69</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>44</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn></math></p>\n<p><strong><em><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>17</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>17</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1102</mn><mo>…</mo></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;A1</em></strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>21</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>17</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>R1</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong><br>OR</strong></p>\n<p>substitution of their <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>21</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>6</mn></math> into their <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>5</mn><mn>882</mn></mfrac><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>44</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn></math> from part (e)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(M1) </strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>21</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>5</mn><mn>882</mn></mfrac><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>44</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>63</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>69</mn><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>63</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; R1</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong><br>Note:</strong> Accept equivalent justification in words, provided both values are seen.<br>Award <em><strong>R1</strong></em> for correct reasoning only if <em><strong>M1</strong></em> has been awarded and their seat coordinates lie outside their equation for the curve.</p>\n<p><br>so the T-shirt cannot reach seat <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mn>40</mn></msub></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>AG</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[5 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"22710190","referenceCode":"24M.3.AHL.TZ1.2f","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Show that it is not possible for the spectator to ever get a T-shirt.","paper":"3","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"f","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 5]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.5—Modelling functions"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}